cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Story2Belief: a computational model of narrative persuasion"
message: "If you use this software or its conceptual framework, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Bakhturina
    given-names: Polina
repository-code: ""
url: ""
abstract: >
  Story2Belief is a research prototype for modeling narrative persuasion as a
  three-layer pipeline: an LLM-based narrative-analysis pipeline producing
  structured text features, a population of AI readers with heterogeneous
  psychological profiles, and a moral-transfer bridge that measures pre/post
  changes in responses to novel moral dilemmas.
keywords:
  - narrative persuasion
  - large language models
  - generative agent-based modeling
  - moral foundations
  - story world absorption
  - computational narratology
